#  Maintained by Tablam project (Mario Mauricio Espinoza Carniglia
#  / mamcx).  225 GH stars.  TablaM is "the practical relational
#  programing language for data-oriented applications" — a
#  RELATIONAL programming language built on Rust, designed around
#  the same RELATIONAL ALGEBRA core that powers SQL but exposed
#  through a clean general-purpose programming syntax (not embedded
#  SQL).  TablaM's tagline: "If you want to do data-engineering
#  stuff, you don't want to write CRUD code, you want to write
#  TRANSFORMATIONS over RELATIONS."  Comparable in ambition to:
#  Microsoft's M-Lang (Power Query M), Datalog dialects, J / K /
#  APL array languages (in spirit, for tabular data), and Rich
#  Hickey's now-abandoned Datomic Pull/Query syntax.  Sister
#  tools: julia (in corpus + STOCK in scientific computing — also
#  data-oriented), r (in corpus — R statistical lang), q (kdb+
#  CLI — KX Systems vector DB; not in corpus), polars (Python/Rust
#  dataframes — in corpus via _polars), duckdb (in corpus via
#  _duckdb), datafusion (Apache DataFusion Rust SQL engine),
#  sqlite3 (in corpus + STOCK), dbgen (data generator).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 15th Rust CLI library — Keisuke
#  Toyota's **seahorse** (ksk001100/seahorse).  Rust ecosystem
#  now has 15 documented CLI libraries — RE-TAKING THE SOLO LEAD
#  as the MOST-DOCUMENTED CLI LANGUAGE in the cross-language
#  taxonomy ahead of Go (14) and TypeScript-Node (14).  🎉 Rust
#  BREAKS the THREE-WAY TIE.
#
#  seahorse (ksk001100/seahorse) is Keisuke Toyota's MINIMAL
#  CLI FRAMEWORK in Rust — explicitly designed as a SPIRITUAL
#  COBRA-FOR-RUST: builder-pattern API with `App::new(name).
#  command(subcmd).flag(flag).action(handler).run(argv)`.  306
#  GH stars.  Used by PaddiM8/kalker (scientific calculator with
#  user-defined variables/functions — 1,877 stars — IN CORPUS via
#  _kalker; existing _kalker completion header note "clap args"
#  is INCORRECT — kalker actually uses seahorse per its Cargo.toml
#  `seahorse = "1.1.1"` dependency), Tablam/TablaM (relational
#  programming language for data — 225 stars), sleepyfran/
#  ts4modmanager (The Sims 4 mod manager), voidcoefficient/
#  hivemind (productivity tools — IN CORPUS via _hivemind, also
#  earlier undocumented seahorse user), and many other smaller
#  Rust CLIs that want a Cobra-like declarative-subcommand
#  framework without clap's weight.
