#  Rust bpaf (functional applicative combinator), R344 Rust google/
#  argh (Google Fuchsia-OS derive-on-struct), R347 Rust RazrFalcon/
#  pico-args (LOW-LEVEL imperative pull parser), R404 Rust matklad/
#  xflags (declarative MACRO block syntax), R407 Rust blyxxyz/
#  lexopt (MINIMAL iterator-based pull parser — match-on-Arg-enum),
#  R410 Rust murarth/gumdrop (zero-dep derive-macro), R413 Rust
#  docopt/docopt.rs (USAGE-STRING-IS-SPEC), R416 Rust rust-lang/
#  getopts (OFFICIAL POSIX-getopt(3) port).  Rust documented
#  libraries so far: clap-derive, bpaf, argh, pico-args, xflags,
#  lexopt, gumdrop, docopt.rs, getopts, seahorse (this round) plus
#  older clap-builder, structopt (deprecated, now clap_derive)...
#  15 total.  seahorse's distinguishing feature vs ALL other Rust
#  libs: seahorse is the ONLY Rust CLI library that explicitly
#  borrows Go's Cobra builder-pattern + subcommand-tree
#  philosophy.  Conceptually similar to Go's cobra/urfave-cli/
#  kingpin (chained-builder + subcommand framework) but in Rust.
#  seahorse's approach: COBRA-FOR-RUST CHAINED-BUILDER with
#  `App::new(name).description.author.version.usage.action.flag.
#  command.run(args)` fluent API + `Command::new(name).description.
#  alias.usage.action.flag.command` recursive subcommand tree +
#  `Flag::new(name, FlagType)` typed flags (Bool/String/Int/Float/
#  Uint) + `Context` query API (`bool_flag/string_flag/int_flag/
#  float_flag/uint_flag` + `args: Vec<String>` positionals) +
#  AUTO --help/--version + INSPIRED BY spf13/cobra Go.  Brings
#  cross-language CLI library taxonomy variant count to 159; Rust
#  ecosystem now has 15 documented CLI libraries — RE-TAKING THE
#  SOLO LEAD as the MOST-DOCUMENTED CLI LANGUAGE in the cross-
#  language taxonomy ahead of Go (14) and TypeScript-Node (14).
#
#  Surface (verbatim from `src/tablam/src/main.rs` seahorse App
#  builder):
#
#  Usage:
#    tablam [command]
#
#  Default action (no subcommand):
#    Launches the TablaM REPL (interactive shell with syntect
#    syntax highlighting, rustyline line editing, history saved
#    to .history.txt in cwd).  REPL commands: "help", "exit"
#    (Ctrl-D / Ctrl-C also exit), or any TablaM source line.
#
#  Subcommands:
#    --file (-f) <FILE.tbl>         Load and run a TablaM source
#                                   file (note the UNUSUAL
#                                   subcommand syntax — TablaM
#                                   models the file mode as a
#                                   seahorse Command with `name
#                                   = "--file"` rather than as a
#                                   flag on the App; resulting
#                                   CLI invocation is
#                                   `tablam --file script.tbl`
#                                   or `tablam -f script.tbl`)
#
#  Auto-generated by seahorse:
#    -h, --help                     Show help
#    -v, --version                  Show TablaM version
#
#  Examples:
#    tablam                                 # Launch REPL
#    tablam --file script.tbl               # Run TablaM script file
#    tablam -f script.tbl                   # Same (short alias)
#    tablam --version                       # Print version
#    tablam --help                          # Show help
#
#  Dup-skipped neighbors during hunt (in corpus or smaller user base,
#  also seahorse users):
#    - kalker (IN CORPUS via _kalker — PaddiM8/kalker scientific
#      calculator 1,877 stars; uses seahorse per Cargo.toml
#      `seahorse = "1.1.1"`; existing _kalker completion's header
#      note "Verified: upstream cli/src/main.rs clap args" is
#      INCORRECT — kalker actually uses seahorse, not clap.  This
#      is an earlier undocumented seahorse user in the corpus;
#      R420 formally documents seahorse via tablam instead since
#      changing _kalker's already-correct flag list isn't needed)
#    - hivemind (IN CORPUS via _hivemind — different `hivemind`
#      tool; voidcoefficient/hivemind 12 stars also uses seahorse
#      but corpus's existing _hivemind is for a different
#      hivemind binary)
#    - ts4modmanager (sleepyfran/ts4modmanager 9 stars — Sims 4
#      mod manager; FUTURE candidate but too niche)
#    - ksk001100/seahorse (the seahorse library repo itself, 306
#      stars — library not a CLI)
# ============================================================================

_tablam() {
  local context state state_descr line
  typeset -A opt_args
  local curcontext="$curcontext"

  _arguments -C \
    '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '(-v --version)'{-v,--version}'[show TablaM version]' \
    '1: :->subcommand' \
    '*:: :->args' && return

  case "$state" in
    subcommand)
      local -a subcmds
      subcmds=(
        '--file:load and run a TablaM source file'
        '-f:load and run a TablaM source file (alias)'
      )
      _describe -t subcommands 'tablam subcommand' subcmds
      ;;
    args)
      case "${words[1]}" in
        --file|-f)
          _arguments -s -S \
            '*:file:_files -g "*.tbl"'
          ;;
      esac
      ;;
  esac
}

_tablam "$@"
